<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Parsing counters() functions</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/syndata.html#parsing-errors" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="To refer to a sequence of nested counters of the same name,.he notation is 'counters(identifier,.tring)' or 'counters(identifier,.tring,.ist-style-type)'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                counter-reset: chapter;
            }
            #p1
            {
                counter-reset: chapter;
            }
            div p:before
            {
                content: counter(chapter);
                counter-increment: chapter;
            }
            #p1:before
            {
                content: counters(chapter,..");
                counter-increment: chapter;
            }
            #p2:before
            {
                content: counters(chapter,..");
                counter-increment: chapter;
            }
            #p3:before
            {
                content: counters(chapter,..",.ower-roman);
                counter-increment: chapter;
            }
            #p4:before
            {
                content: counters(chapter,..",.pper-roman);
                counter-increment: chapter;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the equations below are true.</p>
        <div>
            <p> = 1</p>
            <p id="p1"> = 1.1</p>
            <p id="p2"> = 1.2</p>
            <p id="p3"> = i.iii</p>
            <p id="p4"> = I.IV</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>